  </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Grr.. ninja looters!</span><hr size=1> Tonight my guild helped me take out Captain Rottgrime for my epic.  I played my main 59 bard because I thought she could contribute more than my 53 mage against the magic immune mob.  The pull went well and we handled him with no problem.  I checked him with bard and verified he had the tears and logged onto my mage.  I log in, click on corpse and get the &quot;someone is looting this corpse&quot; message  then the corpse poofs and I see a dark elf running away.  Luckily a friend of mine chased him down and got his name.  This guy claimed he only looted a fine steel longsword, but when pressed further admited he looted the tears.  So a petition and report later I have a guide contacting me.  I am thankful to say the guide was great and thanks to the /report he told me that he is going to recommend that the GM reimburse me the item.  Well, I know its not that hard a fight, and most likely I will get the piece, but I still can't help but be pissed.  Oh well, the GM never did log on so I'll be repetitioning tomorrow.  Just wanted to share my frustrations.<br>
<br>
Annelies Twinclaw, 59 bard<br>
Ilsa Laszlo, 53 mage<br>
Armored Division<br>
Mithaniel Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzolexa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zolexa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 7:30:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grr.. ninja looters!</span><hr size=1> Aye Ilsa, It was a sight to finish the Captain off, target a new mob, just to see a lowlife loot and scamper off with your piece.  I admit chasing him down was a bit fun in a way.  Not like I could tackle him and beat him up. lol. But I was amazed that upon hailing him, he stopped and immidiatly wanted to offer a trade, the piece being no drop wouldn't allow that, so after 4 tries, I told him he just ninja'd our mages epic piece, then he tried to give me the FS sword. Duh! I said no, the blue stone, waited a second and then he said &quot;Oh, I do have it&quot;...can you say /report.  If someone is dumb enough to walk up to a group of 12 in process of killing multiple mobs, and ninja, I guess I'm not surprised he flat out admitted it.  Sometime stupidity is genuinly amusing.  Hopefully you will get the piece, since now both of your pullers are kos and would have to think of new tactics.  Good Luck!<br>
<br>
Zolexa Ravensoul<br>
52 Human Reaver<br>
Officer Armored Division <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzyphyr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zyphyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 537<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 8:00:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grr.. ninja looters!</span><hr size=1> Re-pulling and doing the kill over would have been <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> much</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> faster than a petition... The Captain has a respawn of something like 5 minutes (might be even less than that, it has been a while since I dealt with him).<br>
<br>
<br>
But yes, Ninja-looters need to be taken out and shot. <p><DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:glow(color=FFFF00)"><h4>Zyphyr Runnersbane</h4></div>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44185">Vending Machine and Disciple of Zomm</a><br>
Cult of the Ancient Wyrm<br>
Solusek Ro<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueknor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eknor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 8:24:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ninja Looters</span><hr size=1> Sorry to hear that. I havent been in your position...but could you possibly have had another in your party take the looting position on the corpse while not removing anything, then step away when you arrived with your main to actually loot the corpse?<br>
Eknor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uanneliestwinclaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AnneliesTwinclaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 7:17:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grr.. ninja looters!</span><hr size=1> Our guild has been ninja'd several times in Icewell while gearing out our alts in Royal Velium armor, so usually we do have someone sit on the corpses.  But this time, a few extra mobs had wandered by and we were actually rather heavily engaged.  No one saw someone else hanging around so I think everyone was just trying to finish off the mobs that were left while I switched characters.  <br>
<br>
Anne<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzolexa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zolexa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 10:38:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grr.. ninja looters!</span><hr size=1> The pull tactic we had used depended on the fact that myself and the 2nd relay puller where not KoS.  During the course of the fight and the ensuing engagement following, we had dropped enough in faction to become in fact KoS.  If we do in fact need to pull him again, we shall have to devise a new plan.  We had heard about waiting for the patrol to start out on their rounds during night hours, but the entire time we were there they had never left.  That is why we arranged the pull as we did.<br>
<br>
Zolexa <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=izudin>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#333333>(9/10/02 6:39:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Is this Ninja'ing??</span><hr size=1> I can feel your pain, and hope that you will get the tears soon. However I have a very serious question.<br>
<br>
If I kill a mob, then switch to another char and in the meanwhile someone takes the item of the killed mob, is that really ninja'ing? After all the char who killed the mob isnt around so cant claim his price. Of course in your case it was special because others were around who helped you and watched the incident.<br>
<br>
I think the same situation could happen to me in SK if I played my ranger to find Quillmane, then log on mage to loot the cloak if it should drop. What if someone took the cloak in the meanwhile?? Quill attracts a lot of attention usually...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufarslayer77.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Farslayer77</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#333333>(9/10/02 12:51:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is this Ninja'ing??</span><hr size=1> Friend used her level 3 DE rogue to pull him for  us. This piece is also mquable. However seeing how much a PITA it is to get<br>
a waterstaff I would want this piece myself for turn in. I had<br>
the tears and rain and a nice person mqued her staff with me.<br>
He is a fast respawn we did him 3 times in a row. Also your<br>
puller can /q after pulling and not take a faction hit. 60 Sk friend single pulled him 3 times in a row and /q as rottengrime<br>
was about to die and took no faction hits ).<br>
